-- AIA Hong Kong IPO's Retail Portion Locks Up HK$100 Billion, Standard Says
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2010-10-21T19:58:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-21/aia-hong-kong-ipo-s-retail-portion-locks-up-hk-100-billion-standard-says.html
The retail portion of  AIA Group
Ltd .’s initial public offering in Hong Kong has locked in more
than HK$100 billion, making it the year’s third-most popular
IPO, the Standard said, citing unidentified people.  The Asian unit of  American International Group  is likely to
price its shares at the top end of the HK$18.38 to HK$19.68, the
Hong Kong-based English-language newspaper reported today. The
institutional portion of the offer has locked up $200 billion,
the Standard said.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
